Perl dyndns - A Perl Dynamic DNS (DDNS) update client
-----------------------------------------------------

Map dynamic IP address into your.hostname.example.org. A
cross-platform solution for DHCP ISP-connected users to obtain
permanent DNS, MX, and Web hosting service from a DDNS provider (e.g.
syndns.org). Works anywhere where Perl is installed.

bin/            The program, example configurartion, ChangeLog
                and helper bash setup for project administration
doc/            Program's manual in various formats
etc/            Administarive files; used for install and managing the project

Requirements:   standard Perl, any recent version (5.004+)
Licence     :   GNU GPL v2 or any later version, see COPYING
Homepage    :   http://freshmeat.net/projects/perl-dyndns
Contact     :   <jari.aalto@cante.net>

End of file
